               <head>Release; Higham, etc.; 1347</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111663">Higham</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1347">1347</origDate>.
                        Release from <persName nymRef="Heigham">
                           <forename>Edmund</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Thomas</forename> of <surname>Heigham</surname>
                           </persName> in the parish of <placeName role="person" key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName></persName>, to <persName nymRef="Heigham">
                           <foreign>Amicia</foreign>, daughter of <persName nymRef="Heigham">
                              <forename>Thomas</forename>, son of <persName>
                                 <forename>Thomas</forename> of <surname>Heigham</surname></persName></persName>,</persName> of his right in lands, tenements etc., held by her in Heigham, <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gaislee)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, and <placeName key="place_1083518">Cavenham (Cauenham)</placeName>, as described in a charter of enfeoffment drawn up for her by <persName>Andrew of Swafham</persName>, and <persName>Thomas <surname>Clayton</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName></persName>, chaplains: also in a messuage, building, curtilage, and 5 acres of arable land, which she claims to hold in Heigham, by gift from <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Vsflet</surname>, perpetual vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Honedene</surname></persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fiches</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heigham)</placeName></persName>; which messuage lies next to the tenement of <persName>
                           <forename>Agnes</forename> 
                           <surname>Rolff</surname></persName>, on one side, and to the messuage of <persName>
                           <forename>Edmund</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Thomas</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Thomas</surname></persName></persName>, on the other; and one part of the land and curtilage lies between the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>[Her?]yng</surname>, jun.</persName>, and that of the said Edmund: and 3 acres lie in 'le [com]unne'(?) next to the land of the said Edmund; and one acre at Felleberne. 
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_113011">Thaxted (Thaxstede)</placeName> on the feast of SS. Philip and James, 21 Edw III [1 May 1347].
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Benge</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Cartere</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename> 
                           <surname>Cartere</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_113011">Thaxted (Thoxsteds)</placeName></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> 
                           <surname>Welde</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fiche</surname></persName>, and others.
                        The seal is wanting.
                     </p>
